==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dirige
<hw>Dir"i*ge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. See
<er>Dirge</er>.]</ety> <def>A service for the dead, in the Roman
Catholic Church, being the first antiphon of Matins for the dead, of
which <xex>Dirige</xex> is the first word; a dirge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Evensongs and placebo and <qex>dirige</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wyclif.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Resort, I pray you, unto my sepulture⟦br⟧
To sing my <qex>dirige</qex> with great devotion.</q>
<rj><qau>Lamentation of Mary Magdalene.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dirigent</ent>⟦br⟧
